#week-title("One", "Mercury — The Spirit Principle")

=== Core Teaching

The first of the three philosophical principles is *Mercury*. In the alchemical
sense, this is not the liquid metal of the same name, but the *spirit-principle*:
the universal life force, the volatile, the animating presence that makes a thing
what it is.

Alchemical Mercury is the life-giving energy or essence manifest in all matter. It
is the same in all living things, differing only in the degree of refinement and
the kingdom through which it expresses. In the vegetable kingdom, Mercury is the
same in all plant life; it is found in the alcohol that rises from fermentation.

#doctrine[
  _"Mercury is the Soul of all Metals and Minerals. Without it, neither Sulphur
  nor Salt can exert any power or influence whatsoever. It is the Mover, the
  Universal Animator."_
  #align(right)[— _Golden Chain of Homer_, Part I, Ch. II]
]

Mercury is what rises when you heat a substance — the first thing to depart. It
is the mediator between the soul (Sulphur) and the body (Salt).

=== Topics This Week

- Mercury as the spirit-principle: definitions and distinctions
- The universal life force in the vegetable kingdom
- Why common mercury is not alchemical Mercury
- Mercury as the "Mover" and "Universal Animator"

#inner-work[
  *The Threefold Breath — Right Channel (Mercury)*

  Continue the daily sitting practice established in Month 1. After the Third Eye
  Focus, introduce the first stage of the *Threefold Breath*.

  *The Practice:*
  Sit. Block the left nostril with the ring finger of the right hand. Breathe in
  slowly through the right nostril, imagining the right side of the body filling
  with bright white vapour — clear, light, and volatile. Breathe out white vapour.
  Repeat three times.

  This white vapour represents the Mercury principle within the Microcosm. Observe
  its quality: is it light? Does it feel expansive or restless? Record your
  observations in the journal.

  *Numerology — The Number 1:*
  Study the number 1 as a living philosophical principle. It is the pioneer, the
  undifferentiated creative impulse — the Mercury principle as pure originating
  force. Nothing has yet been given form; the one acts without resistance.
]

